650.300.  Definitions. — As used in sections 650.300 to 650.310, the following terms shall mean:
  (1)  "Catastrophic crime", a violation of section 574.080*;
  (2)  "Office", the office for victims of crime;
  (3)  "Private agency", a private agency as defined in section 595.010;
  (4)  "Public agency", a public agency as defined in section 595.010;
  (5)  "Victim of crime", a person afforded rights as a victim or entitled to compensation or services as a victim pursuant to chapter 595.
(L. 2001 S.B. 267) 
*Section 569.070 was transferred to section 574.080 by S.B. 491, 2014, effective 1-01-17.
